Database: Collection of data which holds data in form of Tables.

Table: A way of storing data in form of rows and columns. 

Database is used to store, access and manipulate the data.

Types of Databases: Relational Database vs Non Relational or NoSQL Database

->Relational Database: Data is stored in the form of rows and columns(Tables). Multiple tables have relations between them.
  Ex: MySQL, SQL Server, PostreSQL, SQLite, MariaDB 

->NoSQL: Data is stored in form of Key value pairs, Documents and Graph. Not in rows and columns. Two tables do not have relation between them.
  Ex: Hbase, MangoDB, Cassandra

Focus on MySQL.

SQL - Structured Query Language - A way to communicate with Relational database(MySQL). It is used to query a relational Db.

Create a DB
-> CREATE DATABASE database_name;

USE database
-> USE database_name;

Create Table
-> CREATE TABLE table_name(
          column_name1 datatype,
          column_name2 datatype,
          column_name3 datatype
          );
 
Data Types:

Int - Numeric values
Varchar - strings upto 255 characters

DROP table
-> DROP TABLE Student;

Drop DB
-> DROP DATABASE;



